-- Ex-Citi CEO Pandit, partner take stake in India's JM Financial
-- 
-- Thu May 16, 2013 10:40am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/05/16/us-financial-vikram-pandit-idUSBRE94F0O220130516

 

 MUMBAI  (Reuters) - India's JM Financial Ltd ( JMSH.NS ) says former Citi Chief Executive Vikram Pandit and his business partner, Hari Aiyer are to buy a 3 percent equity stake in the financial services company through an issue of warrants. 
 JM Financial also said it would set up a fund jointly with Pandit's firm to buy distressed assets. The fund is targeting an initial capitalization of $100 million, JM Financial said in a statement late on Thursday. (Reporting by Aditi Shah. Editing by Jane Merriman)